org.threadly.concurrent.collections

Class DynamicDelayQueue<T extends java.util.concurrent.Delayed>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.threadly.concurrent.collections.DynamicDelayQueue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Parameter to indicate what type of item is contained in the queue
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue<T>, java.util.Queue<T>
    Deprecated. 
    There is no replacement, please open a github issue if this class is useful to you

    @Deprecated
public class DynamicDelayQueue<T extends java.util.concurrent.Delayed>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Queue<T>, java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue<T>

    This queue is very similar to DelayQueue but has one major difference. This queue is designed around the idea that items can change their delay. Items enter the queue with Long.MAX_VALUE delay, and then will just call reposition once they know when their next execution time is.

    In order to allow an item to be repositioned like this, the item must implement the DynamicDelayedUpdater interface.

    Since:
    1.0.0

      • reposition

        public void reposition(T e,
                       long newDelayInMillis,
                       DynamicDelayedUpdater updater)
        Deprecated. 
        Called to reposition an item in the queue which's delay wants to be updated since original insertion (or was originally inserted as addLast(Delayed)). It is expected that this function will be called to reposition before the items delay time is updated in the Delayed.getDelay(TimeUnit) call. Once the queue is ready for the item to update, it will call DynamicDelayedUpdater.allowDelayUpdate() on the provided updater. This call to DynamicDelayedUpdater.allowDelayUpdate()} will happen before the reposition call returns.
        Parameters:
        e - item currently in the queue
        newDelayInMillis - delay time that e will be updated to after reposition
        updater - class to call into when queue is ready for item to update delay
